# cys-agi + Karpathy guidelines

Merged with [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Full skill stub: [.agents/skills/cys-agi-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md](../skills/cys-agi-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md). On errors: [cys-agi-agent-kaizen.mdc](cys-agi-agent-kaizen.mdc).

**Tradeoff:** Caution over speed on non-trivial work.

## Four principles (cys-agi mapping)

| # | Principle | In this repo |
|---|-----------|--------------|
| 1 | **Think before coding** | Read MASTER_PLAN + phase scope; identify layer (`ingress`, `workers`, `agents`, `cys_core/domain`) |
| 2 | **Simplicity first** | KISS; no speculative features beyond the phase |
| 3 | **Surgical changes** | Diff ⊆ phase plan; ≤5 files; critic rejects scope creep |
| 4 | **Goal-driven execution** | Phase DoD → `./scripts/pytest_batches.sh`; loop until green |

## Planning rhythm

1. Master plan → 2. Phase plan → 3. Branch `cys-agi/phase-NN-slug` → 4. Implement → 5. PR → 6. **Critic** → 7. Merge → update master plan.

## Critic quick checks

- Every hunk traces to phase plan or explicit user ask.
- No secrets in commits; tool allowlists and HITL unchanged without approval.
- Adversarial tests cited when security paths touched.
